				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well. Like all paladins i have spent counltess hours dreaming of the day when i could obtain this fine weapon. I, and a few of my faithful guildmates, members of the United Norrathian Brotherhood, have spent nearly 30 hours in shifts camping this blade, hunting the froggie that might yeild it to me. here are some facts(yes they seem to hold true in 30 hours of &quot;testing&quot;)<BR>
<BR>
1. this will be one of the most delicate camps you will ever encounter. if you keep the WHOLE room clear you will live. let them restack and you die. <BR>
2.there are a total of 19 frogs that will come at you. the 13 in the circular room. the 2 in the &quot;bar&quot; the 2 in the hall and 2 nearest the gate/wall thing. <BR>
3. All but the lord and a select few will be a nice blue to a lvl 30.<BR>
4. the lord doesnt seem to spawn if the entire set of at least 17 (not 2 by gate) are not dead.<BR>
His PH will however pop, he doesnt seem to like a crowded room. =)<BR>
5.  this camp will be long. (execpt for you Kordolar) we have been here so long i have taken up drinking. when we started this camp my AT was 2 its now maxed at 155. =/<BR>
6.you WILL share with a lvl 50 caster at some point or at least &quot;have words&quot;.<BR>
and lastly,<BR>
7. he does not LoH if hes not carrying the GB. thats a nice tell-tale sign. if he LoHes then ya better get rollin and pray you got good charaisma.<BR>
<BR>
anyway, thats my 2cp of observation. take it or leave it. thats what i saw. BTW in 31.25 hrs ive seen 6 lords. <BR>
Carrek Holyblade<BR>
&quot;Since when do wizzies wield pally only swords? Damn, i chose the wrong class...&quot;<BR>
30th circle pal of (both) brells.
